org.apparatus_templi

Class Prefs

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apparatus_templi.Prefs

  • public class Prefs
extends Object
    A singleton pattern that maintains a map of default preferences. Contains methods to read preferences from a Properties, to set preferences in memory, and to write preferences back to disk. from configuration file.
    Author:
    Jonathan Nelson

    • Method Detail

      • isCredentialsSet

        public static boolean isCredentialsSet()
        Checks that the web service has a username and password set.
        Returns:
        true if both a username and password have been set (not null and not empty), false otherwise

      • readPreferences

        public void readPreferences(String configFile)
        Reads all preferences from the given configFile. If the given file can not be read then the default preferences are used.
        Parameters:
        configFile -

      • getPreference

        public String getPreference(String key)
        Retuns the preferences associated with the given key.
        Parameters:
        key - the name of the preference to return. A set of keys is available for use in the Prefs.Keys class.

      • getPreferenceDesc

        public String getPreferenceDesc(String key)
        Returns a long description for the given preference.
        Parameters:
        key - the preference value to return a description for. Valid keys are listed in Prefs.Keys
        Returns:
        a long String description of the requested preference, or null if the preference has no description or is unknown.

      • getPreferenceName

        public String getPreferenceName(String key)
        Returns a human readable name for the given preference.
        Parameters:
        key - the preference value to return a short name for. Valid keys are listed in Prefs.Keys
        Returns:
        a short name (one to three words) of the requested preference, or null if the preference has no name or is unknown.

      • getDefPreference

        public String getDefPreference(String key)
        Returns the default value for the requested preference.
        Parameters:
        key - the preference value to return a default value for. Valid keys are listed in Prefs.Keys
        Returns:
        the default value for the requested preference, or null if the preference has no default value or is unknown.

      • getDefPreferencesMap

        HashMap<String,String> getDefPreferencesMap()
        Returns a deep copy of the default preferences map.

      • putPreference

        public void putPreference(String key,
                 String value)
        Update the value of a preference. Updating the preference value will only update the preference resident in memory. To store the preference permanently savePreferences(HashMap) must be used.
        Parameters:
        key - the name of the preference to update. A set of keys is available for use in the Prefs.Keys class.
        value - the value of the preference.

      • getPreferencesMap

        public HashMap<String,String> getPreferencesMap()
        Returns a copy of the current preferences map. Since the returned map is a copy changes will not be reflected in the saved preferences.

      • savePreferences

        public boolean savePreferences(HashMap<String,String> prefs)
        Writes the given preferences back to the config file. If any preference is undefined in the given map then the default preference will be written. Keys that do not map to a known value in Prefs.Keys will also be written to the file.
        Parameters:
        prefs - a HashMap of key/value pairs to write back to the preferences file.
